Color and pattern. Ground color pale yellowish or whitish. Eye patches dark blue to black. Frontal and inter-antennal areas of head dark blue; narrow blue pigment line present behind eyes and reach thoraces along lateral borders of head. Antennal segments I & II lightly pigmented, deeply pigmented on Ant. III and IV. Terga of Th. II and III with median large dark spots and dark lateral margins. Abd. III largely dark, with paler areas near lateral margins. Abd. IV with 2 transverse bands, one made of scattered pale blue pigment on the anterior 1 / 3 and a wide deep blue band on the posterior 1 / 4 . Latero-posterior margins of Abd. IV dark. Lateral sides of Abd. V pale blue. Abd. VI without pigment. Hind leg with dark pigment on trochanter and femur, other leg segments sparsely pigmented (
Fig. 1
).

Head. Eyes 8 + 8 , ocelli A–F subequal, G and H much smaller and sometimes difficult to see. 3 small setae surrounded by eyes D–H (
Fig. 2
). Antennae 2.7–4.1 times as long as cephalic diagonal; ratios of Ant. I–IV as 1 / 1.2–1.8 / 1–1.5 / 1.5–3.3 . Ant. IV with bilobed apical vesicle (
Fig. 3
).

Chaetotaxy. Dorsal chaetotaxy of head (
Jordana & Baquero 2005
;
Soto-Adames 2008
) with 3 setae in area H 1 (An 2 , An 3 a, An 3 ), 1 seta in area H 2 (A 5 ), 3 setae in area H 4 (S 1 , S 3 , S 4 ), and 2 setae in area H 5 (Ps 2 , Ps 5 ); seta S’0 in area H 3 absent (
Fig. 2
,). Head macrochaetotaxy formula: 3 – 1 – 0–3 – 2 . Labral setal formula as 4 /5,5,4 (
Fig. 4
). Seta a0 and a 1 subequal but slightly longer than seta a 2 ; seta b0 and b 1 subequal but slightly longer than seta b 2 ; c 1 and b 2 subequal but slightly longer than c 2 ; a 1 , a 2 and a 3 longer than other setae (
Fig. 4
). Setal formula of labial triangle as M, R, E, L 1 , L 2 ; seta R 0.66–0.75 times as long as M; E smooth (mostly), or both E and L 1 smooth (
Fig. 5
). All postlabial setae (see
Chen & Christiansen 1993
) ciliate, H 1 , H 2 , H 3 , H 4 subequal but slightly longer than G 1 , G 2 , G 3 , G 4 . Setae G 1 slightly longer than G 2 , G 3 and G 4 ; G 2 and G 4 subequal but slightly shorter than G 3 . Setae X,
X 2
,
X 3
subequal but slightly shorter than
X 4
; these slightly shorter than other setae. (
Fig. 5
). None of the setae expanded or leaf-like.

Legs. Coxal macrochaetal formula as 3 / 4 ( 5 ) +2, 3/ 4 + 2 , some mesochaetae also present on coxa of leg III (
Fig. 9
). Trochanteral organ developed only in the hind leg, composed of 50–84 stiff, smooth setae, 18–20 of them arranged in arms, 32–64 between arms (Fig. 10 ). Inner tibiotarsal differentiated setae slightly ciliate and clearly different from other normal coarsely ciliate setae. Tenent hair strongly clavate and slightly longer than inner edge of unguis. Unguis with 3 small inner teeth, basal paired teeth subequal. Outer edge of unguiculus smooth without large tooth (Fig. 11 ).
